attributes.gcd: Refers to the unique identifier of the account group to which this account is assigned. Account group is a grouping of accounts based on certain criteria. Examples of account group types include household, statement bundling etc.
Refers to the market value of holdings under management in the account group as of the business data submission, expressed in base currency.

attributes.logicalName: Account Group Relationship Head Net Worth Amount
attributes.gcd: Refers to the net worth of the client relationship to which this account group is associated expressed in base currency.

attributes.logicalName: Account Group Weighted Average Risk Rating
attributes.gcd: This column stores the total weighted average risk rating i.e. WARR for an account group. It is based on the sum of all individual weighted average risk ratings for all positions in the account group.
